{"TopicId":156105,"ForumId":21,"TopicTitle":"Mine the seafloor on kerbin ... anywhere","CreatedByName":"Azimech","CreatedById":50750,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-07T06:28:32Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Azimech","CreatedById":50750,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-07T06:28:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022HRA4wI3.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022564\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/HRA4wI3.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022mY9k7hv.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022564\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/mY9k7hv.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022wb7d17C.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022564\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/wb7d17C.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022JdtQo5I.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022564\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/JdtQo5I.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMore pictures: \u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/a/Iohgy\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://imgur.com/a/Iohgy\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHuge self-propelled mining platform, can drill for ore on any sea at maximum depth.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUsing the power of autostruts it\u0027s possible now to keep a drill head connected to a ship and just let it sink to any depth. On Kerbin the max depth is ~1200m. The \u0022cable\u0022 is even longer than that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, part count is high. The \u0022cable\u0022 has most of it. You can reduce part count by deleting stuff from the superstructure you don\u0027t need. For example the walkway has a bunch of emergency lights (they\u0027re just folded up ladders).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe \u003Cabbr title=\u0022In-Situ Resource Utilization\u0022\u003EISRU\u003C/abbr\u003E is located behind the crew cabin.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease notice: \u0022Part Pressure Limits\u0022 needs to be OFF (Difficulty options -\u0026gt; advanced).\u003Cbr\u003E\nAlso, you need advanced tweakables enabled.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow to operate:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1. Sail to the location with ore.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2. Use the console to visualize the autostruts (Alt-F12 -\u0026gt; Physics).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3. Disable all the autostruts on the \u0022cable\u0022. Doesn\u0027t matter which sequence.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n4. The drill starts sinking. This takes time. You can speed it up using physics acceleration (ALT- \u0026gt;). Do not use more than 3x.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n5. Make sure you enable the fuel cells, the solar panel and the radiator.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n6. Normal time acceleration resets the \u0022cable\u0022 and drill to it\u0027s original location! Also when moving out of physics range or going back to menu.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n7. Use this to your advantage. If you\u0027re done drilling, set a number of \u0022cable\u0022 elements and the drill to \u0022Autostrut: Heaviest Part\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n8. With the cable extended, use \u0022Aim Camera\u0022 to navigate along it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHave fun!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh and forget about Laythe. The seas over there are more than twice as deep.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDownload link: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://kerbalx.com/Azimech/77I--Offshore-Mining-Platform-v10\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://kerbalx.com/Azimech/77I--Offshore-Mining-Platform-v10\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DMSP","CreatedById":124853,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-07T10:14:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSomeone was mad at this... I like it tons though. Laythe operations may rely on this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Azimech","CreatedById":50750,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-07T14:54:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222947534\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156105\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221486462458\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022124853\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DMSP\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, DMSP said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSomeone was mad at this... I like it tons though. Laythe operations may rely on this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt would mean operations near the shores though, severely limiting its usefulness. Was a big disappointment when I discovered it. With an average depth of over 2km it would require a really huge \u0022cable\u0022 and an even larger ship. And how would we get something like that into \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Low Kerbin Orbit\u0022\u003ELKO\u003C/abbr\u003E ... I think this one would already be problematic.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWho knows ... maybe Squad would like the idea and raise the seafloor in a future update \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/167737-uomocapra/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022167737\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/167737-uomocapra/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@UomoCapra\u003C/a\u003E?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Raven.","CreatedById":99340,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-07T15:06:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat helicopter looks pretty sweet!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Azimech","CreatedById":50750,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-07T15:14:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222947704\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156105\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221486480014\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002299340\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Raven.\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, Raven. said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat helicopter looks pretty sweet!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks, that\u0027s the Azi15 Archon II. It isn\u0027t released yet.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mesklin","CreatedById":73898,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-07T16:13:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt is really amazing thing. Second picture is great, it remembered me \u0022The Abyss\u0022 movie.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Azimech","CreatedById":50750,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-07T16:14:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222947759\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156105\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221486483996\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273898\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Mesklin\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Mesklin said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt is really amazing thing. Second picture is great, it remembered me \u0022The Abyss\u0022 movie.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNice reference!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Majorjim!","CreatedById":61954,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-07T16:16:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222947759\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156105\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221486483996\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273898\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Mesklin\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, Mesklin said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\u0022The Abyss\u0022 movie.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ci\u003E\u0027The crane! We lost the crane! It\u0027s on it\u0027s\u00A0way down to you!\u0027\u003C/i\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0One of\u00A0my all time favourite movies.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0Nice idea using the parts like that man.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-02-07T16:18:27Z\u0022 title=\u002202/07/2017 04:18  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 7, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Majorjim!\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Castille7","CreatedById":101668,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-08T02:40:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOnce again another great creative build! \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/61954-majorjim/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u00